name: Flower
description: Waratah, or Telopea speciosissima, usually grows in bushland areas around Newcastle and flowers in the spring.

name: Miners Lamp
description: Coal mining in Australia began near Nobbys Head in Newcastle in the 1790s. Mine lamps are used to light the road in dark mining areas.

name: Compass
description: From ancient times to the present, different ships on lake macquarie have needed a compass to guide them.

name: Surfboard
description: Surfing is an exciting sport and a symbol of freedom. There are plenty of surf beaches around Lake Macquarie.
